Valid for W15A 14W37 Sprint: Updates - PSS: GPEH CPI Improvement additional changes – Phase 1, 248/10268-FCP1217060.(Automated CPI Production) CPI text added in the last column in sheets: InternalEvents, ExternalEvents, EventParams, and EventParamValues
For detailed update information, check file "Detailed update info - 10_1551_Rev B1" attached to this document.

Valid for W15A 14W37 Sprint: Updates - PSS: Traffic Aware Power Save, 240/102 68-FCP 121 7060 - PSS: GPEH CPI Improvement – Phase 1, 248/10268-FCP1217060.(Automated CPI Production) - Editorial updates conisdering the CPI automated production
For detailed update information, check file "Detailed update info - 10_1551_Rev B" attached to this document.

Valid for W15A 14W31 Sprint: Updates - Changed document number from 10/1551-AXD 105 03/1 to 10/1551-AXD 105 03 (Previous revision levels are based on Doc No: 10/1551-AXD 105 03/1) - Editorial updates (RNC internal)
For detailed update information, check file "Detailed update info - 10_1551_Rev A" attached to this document.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_ACCURACY_FULFILMENT_INDICATOR
parametertype.description: The value of the IE accuracy fulfilment indicator in the message LOCATION REPORT.
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_ACHIEVED_HORIZONTAL_ACCURACY
parametertype.description: In case the reported shape is Ellipsoid Point with Uncertainly circle, this parameter shall be set equal to the coded uncertainty radius of that shape.
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. If the Cell Id method is selected, this parameter is calculated based on the estimated Cell Id area; in other words, equal to round(ln(1+1/10*sqrt (area/pi))/ln(1.1)). If the A-GPS method is selected this parameter is equal to the calculated uncertaintyCode or horizontalUncertainty parameters. If neither of these parameters are available, the event parameter must be set to invalid.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_ACHIEVED_VERTICAL_ACCURACY
parametertype.description: Uncertainty Altitude according to the MEASUREMENT REPORT (RRC) message. 128 means that the configurable parameter AgpsPositioning.uncertaintyAltitude is used instead of the IE in the RRC message.
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. Uncertainty Altitude according to the Measurement Report (RRC) message. The value 128 means that the configurable parameter AgpsPositioning.uncertaintyAltitude is used instead of the IE in the RRC message.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_DL_QUALITY_MEAS1_TARGET_CELL
parametertype.description: In general the HO type is determined by the combination of the parameters EVENT_PARAM_EVALUATION_CASE and EVENT_PARAM_PROCEDURE_INDICATOR. For applicable parameter values, see their respective parameter description. Parameter representation for IRATHO: This parameter represents RSSI (Range: 0..63, Resolution: See 3GPP spec, Unit: See 3GPP spec). 3GPP spec 45.008 specifies the mapping between the reported value and the actual physical measured value, where RXLEV corresponds to RSSI. The measured signal level shall be mapped to an RXLEV value between 0 and 63, as follows (where SCALE equals '0' when ordering a 3a measurement, therefore excluded below): RXLEV 0 = less than ‑110 dBm RXLEV 1 = ‑110 dBm to ‑109 dBm RXLEV 2 = ‑109 dBm to ‑108 dBm : : RXLEV 62 = ‑49 dBm to ‑48 dBm RXLEV 63 = greater than ‑48 dBm Parameter representation for IRATCC: This parameter represents RSSI. Same definition as for IRATHO Parameter representation for GAN HO: This parameter represents RSSI. Same definition as for IRATHO Parameter representation for CNHHO: This parameter represents CPICH Ec/N0 (Range: 0..49, Resolution: 0.5, Unit: dB (the physical measured value is in dB). See 3GPP spec 25.133 for mapping between reported value and the actual physical measured value. The reporting range is for CPICH Ec/Eo is from -24 ...0 dB, resolution 0.5.) Parameter representation for IFHO: This parameter represents CPICH Ec/N0. Same definition as for CNHHO.
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_DL_QUALITY_MEAS2_TARGET_CELL
parametertype.description: In general the HO type is determined by the combination of the parameters EVENT_PARAM_EVALUATION_CASE and EVENT_PARAM_PROCEDURE_INDICATOR. For applicable parameter values, see their respective parameter description. Parameter representation for IRATHO: This parameter is N/A. Parameter representation for IRATCC: This parameter is N/A. Parameter representation for GAN HO: This parameter is N/A. Parameter representation for CNHHO: This parameter represents CPICH RSCP (Range: 0..91, Resolution: 1, Unit: dBm (the physical measured value is in dBm)). See 3GPP spec 25.133 for mapping between reported value and the actual physical measured value. The reporting range is for CPICH RSCP is from -115 ...-25 dBm, resolution 1. Parameter representation for IFHO: This parameter represents CPICH RSCP (Same definition as for CNHHO)
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. In general, the HO type is determined by the combination of the parameters EVENT_PARAM_EVALUATION_CASE and EVENT_PARAM_PROCEDURE_INDICATOR. For applicable parameter values, see their respective parameter description. Parameter representation for IRATHO: This parameter is N/A. Parameter representation for IRATCC: This parameter is N/A. Parameter representation for GAN HO: This parameter is N/A. Parameter representation for CNHHO: This parameter represents CPICH RSCP (Range: 0..91, Resolution: 1, Unit: dBm (the physical measured value is in dBm)). See 3GPP spec 25.133 for mapping between reported value and the actual physical measured value. The reporting range is for CPICH RSCP is from -115 ...-25 dBm, resolution 1. Parameter representation for IFHO: This parameter represents CPICH RSCP, same definition as for CNHHO.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_IFLS_RESULT_LAST_CAP_EVALUATED
parametertype.description: The last capabilities evaluated by IFLS. This parameter will be presented as a bit map value. Only the first 7 bits (LSB) are used, the rest are spare. For details on bitfield defintions, check the EventParamBitfieldDef sheet.
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. The last capabilities evaluated by IFLS. This parameter is presented as a bit map value. Only the first 9 bits (LSB) are used, the rest is spare. Bit 0 indicates if MC is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No Multi Carrier evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=Multi Carrier evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 1 indicates if Dual-band MC is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No Dual-band Multi Carrier evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=Dual-band Multi Carrier evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 2 indicates if MIMO is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No MMO evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=MMO evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 3 indicates if EUL is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No EUL evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=EUL evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 4 indicates if HS is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No HS evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=HS evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 5 indicates if CPC is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No CPC evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=CPC evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 6 indicates if 64QAM is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No 64QAM evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=64QAM evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 7 indicates if 3MC is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No 3MC evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=3MC evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 8 indicates if Dual-band 3MC is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No Dual-band 3MC evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=Dual-band 3MC evaluation during HS IFLS. Bits 9-15 are spare and is always be 0.

parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. Indicate if a new cell is selected after IFLS evaluation.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_IMEISV
parametertype.description: International Mobile Equipment Identity Software Version IMEI-SV is built up by 16 digits in BCD (Binary Coded Decimal) format, each digit represented by 4 bits, Digit 1 is the MSD (Most Significant Digit = leftmost Digit) and Digit 16 is the LSD (Least Significant Digit = rightmost Digit): - bit[60..63] = Digit 1, where bit[63] is the leftmost bit and also the Most Significant Bit (MSB) - bit[56..59] = Digit 2 - ... - bit[0..3] = Digit 16, where bit[0] is the rightmost bit and also the Least Significant Bit (LSB)
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. International Mobile Equipment Identity Software Version IMEI-SV is built up by 16 digits in BCD (Binary Coded Decimal) format, each digit represented by 4 bits, Digit 1 is the MSD (Most Significant Digit = leftmost Digit) and Digit 16 is the LSD (Least Significant Digit = rightmost Digit): - bit[60..63] = Digit 1, where bit[63] is the leftmost bit and also the Most Significant Bit (MSB) - bit[56..59] = Digit 2 - ... - bit[0..3] = Digit 16, where bit[0] is the rightmost bit and also the Least Significant Bit (LSB) .

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_IMSI
parametertype.description: International Mobile Subscriber Identity IMSI is built up by 15 digits in BCD (Binary Coded Decimal) format, each digit represented by 4 bits, where Digit 1 is the MSD (Most Significant Digit = leftmost Digit) and Digit 15 is the LSD (Least Significant Digit = rightmost Digit): - bit[56..59] = Digit 1, where bit[59] is the leftmost bit and also the Most Significant Bit (MSB) - bit[52..55] = Digit 2 - ... - bit[0..3] = Digit 15, where bit[0] is the rightmost bit and also the Least Significant Bit (LSB)
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. International Mobile Subscriber Identity (IMSI), 15 digits BCD , each digit represented by 4 bits. IMSI, BCD encoded, digits 1-15: bits 56-59=most sign digit (Digit 1), ..., bits 0-3=least sign digit (Digit 15). Most Significant Digit (MSD)=leftmost digit (Digit 1); Most Significant Bit (MSB)=leftmost bit (bit position 59). EVENT_PARAM_IMSI = EVENT_PARAM_IMSI_1 + EVENT_PARAM_IMSI_2. EVENT_PARAM_IMSI_1 (32 bits) is the left 8 digits of IMSI in BCD format, digits 1-8: bits 28-31=most sign digit (Digit 1), ..., bits 0-3=least sign digit (Digit 8). Most Significant Digit (MSD)=leftmost digit (Digit 1). Most Significant Bit (MSB)=leftmost bit (bit position 31). EVENT_PARAM_IMSI_2 (32 bits) is the right 7 digits of IMSI in BCD format, digits 9-15: bits 28-31=padding bits, bits 24-27=most sign digit (Digit 9), ..,bits 0-3 = least sign digit (Digit 15). Most Significant Digit (MSD)=leftmost digit (Digit 9); Most Significant Bit (MSB)=leftmost bit (bit position 31).

parametertype.description: SIR error DL Tx code power UL interference DL Tx CarrierPower Non HighSpeed Power HSDSCH Required Power EUL scheduled rate as reported by the RBS
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. Measured value for the related measurement type according to the parameter EVENT_PARAM_MEASURED_ENTITY (SIR error, DL Tx code power, UL interference, DL Tx CarrierPower, Non HighSpeed Power, HSDSCH Required Power). See 3GPP TS 25.133 for updated definitions. The figures here are taken from 3GPP TS 25.133 V5.17.0 (2005-12), 25133-5h0. Ranges for the reported values per measurement type are as follows: SIR Error range: 0..125 (measurement range -31..31, unit: dB, resolution: 0.5) DL Tx code power, range: 0..127 (measurement range -10..46, unit: dBm, resolution: 0.5. Reported values below 10 is mapped to -10 dBm while reported values above 122 is mapped to 46 dBm) UL interference range: 0..621 (Received total wideband power = RTWP), measurement range: -112..-50 dBm, (unit: dBm, resolution: 0.1) DL Tx CarrierPower range: 0..100 (unit: %, resolution: 0.1) HSDSCH_REQUIRED_POWER, range: 0..100 (unit: %, resolution: 0.1) NON_HS_POWER, range: 0..100 (unit: %, resolution: 0.1) EUL scheduled rate as reported by the RBS.

Any Invalid Parameter A parameter without a valid value to report at the time of event reporting is filled with 1s, also referred to as the value EVENT_VALUE_INVALID. A parameter does not have to have any value to report. This happens either when no value is applicable to the event, or there is no value available at the time of event reporting. Most parameter have an extra bit (the most significant bit, that is, the leftmost one) in addition to what is required for the parameter value range called the validity bit. It is used together with the second most significant bit to indicate whether the parameter value is Available / Not Available or Not Applicable. If the two most significant bits are 11, the value is interpreted as Not Applicable. If the two most significant bits are 10, the value is interpreted as Not Available. With a 3-bit parameter (including one validity bit), the parameter value range of 0..3, the following applies: -Not Applicable = 111 -Not Available = 100

parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. If the reported shape is Ellipsoid Arc, this parameter is set equal to the coded offset angle of the Ellipsoid Arc.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_ORIENTATION_MAJOR_AXIS
parametertype.description: Orientation of major axis. The relation between the value (N) and the angle (a) in degrees it describes is 2N = a 2*(N+1)
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. Orientation of major axis. The relation between the value (N) and the angle (a) in degrees it describes is 2N = a 2*(N+1).

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_ORIGINATING_STATE

parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. Originating state at indication of CS or PS call setup.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_OVERLOAD_LEVEL
parametertype.description: Overload Level
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. Overload Level.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_PATHLOSS
parametertype.description: Pathloss used by Serving HS-DSCH Cell Selection. If selected cell is best cell, pathloss should be set to invalid_value
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. Pathloss used by Serving HS-DSCH Cell Selection. If selected cell is best cell, pathloss is set to invalid value (EVENT_VALLUE_INVALID). The value is reported in the range 15..170 dB with a resolution of 1.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_PCAP_ERROR_TYPE

parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. Indicates the reason for the PCAP signalling protocol error.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_PDU_TYPE
parametertype.description: Direction and logical channel used for RRC messages
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. Direction and logical channel used for RRC messages.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_PENDING_AFTER_TRIGGER
parametertype.description: The number of CRCs to received after that the event evaluation start again and a new INTERNAL_EVENT_5A can be triggered (a new event can not be triggered until Pending after trigger CRCs have been received).
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. The number of CRCs to received after that the event evaluation start again and a new INTERNAL_EVENT_5A can be triggered (a new event cannot be triggered until Pending after trigger CRCs is received).

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_REQ_RNC_MODULE_ID
parametertype.description: ID of RNC module where the requesting UE context is allocated Bit 1 the first bit (leftmost) is used as validity bit! Bit 2..6 (range 0..31) is used to represent Member ID (1..31) in RNC in pool (if all 5 bits in 2 .. 6 are 00000 ” this means the Member ID part is 'Not Applicable', When that happens RNC_MODULE_ID is not part of a member in RNC in-pool, instead belongs to a traditional RNC HW configuration. Bit 7..24 (range 0..262143) is used to represent RNC_MODULE_ID
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. ID of RNC module where the requesting UE context is allocated. Bit 1 the first bit (leftmost) is used as validity bit. Bit 2..6 (range 0..31) is used to represent Member ID (1..31) in RNC in pool. If all 5 bits in 2..6 are 00000 this means the Member ID part is Not Applicable . When that happens RNC_MODULE_ID is not part of a member in RNC in-pool, instead belongs to a traditional RNC HW configuration. Bit 7..24 (range 0..262143) is used to represent RNC_MODULE_ID.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_RESOURCE
parametertype.description: The resource that triggered the load control action presented as a bitmap value This parameter will be presented as a bit map value. Bit 0 - RN DL Power; Bit 1 - RN DL ASE; Bit 2 - RN DL Code; Bit 3 - RN DL RBS HW; Bit 4 - RN DL HS users; Bit 5 - RN UL ASE; Bit 6 - RN UL RBS HW Bit 7 - RN UL Serving Cell EUL users; Bit 8 - RN UL Serving Cell EUL 2m TTI users; Bit 9 - TN DL IUB; Bit 10 - TN UL IUB; Bit 11-15 are spare and will always be 0 All bits set to zero indicates 'Not applicable'
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. The resource that triggered the load control action presented as a bitmap value. Bit 0 - RN DL Power; Bit 1 - RN DL ASE; Bit 2 - RN DL Code; Bit 3 - RN DL RBS HW; Bit 4 - RN DL HS users; Bit 5 - RN UL ASE; Bit 6 - RN UL RBS HW Bit 7 - RN UL Serving Cell EUL users Bit 8 - RN UL Serving Cell EUL 2m TTI users; Bit 9 - TN DL IUB; Bit 10 - TN UL IUB; Bit 11-15 are spare and are always 0. All bits set to zero indicate 'Not applicable'.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_RNC_MODULE_ID
parametertype.description: Id of RNC module ID where the cell is allocated Bit 0 the first bit (leftmost) is used as validity bit Bit 1..5 (range 0..31) is used to represent Member ID (1..31) in RNC in pool Bit 6..23 (range 0..262143) is used to represent RNC_MODULE_ID Note: If all 5 bits in 1 .. 5 are 00000 ” the Member ID part is 'Not Applicable', meaning that the RNC module belongs to a traditional RNC HW configuration and is not part of an RNC in pool configuration.
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_RNC_MP_ID
parametertype.description: The identity of the Main Processor (MP) where an error situation has impact on ongoing event recordings. The MP can be of type Module, Central, RANAP, RNSAP or O M. Bit 1 the first bit (leftmost) is used as validity bit! Bit 2..6 (range 0..31) is used to represent Member ID (1..31) in RNC in pool (if all 5 bits in 2 .. 6 are 00000 ” this means the Member ID part is 'Not Applicable', When that happens RNC_MP_ID is not part of a member in RNC in-pool, instead belongs to a traditional RNC HW configuration. Bit 7..24 (range 0..262143) is used to represent RNC_MP_ID
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. The identity of the MP where an error situation has an impact on ongoing event recordings. The MP can be of type Module, Central, RANAP, RNSAP, and O M Bit 1 the first bit (leftmost) is used as validity bit. Bit 2..6 (range 0..31) is used to represent Member ID(1..31) in RNC in pool. If all 5 bits in 2..6 are 00000 this means the Member ID part is Not Applicable . When that happens RNC_MP_ID is not part of a member in RNC in-pool, instead belongs to a traditional RNC HW configuration. Bit 7..24 (range 0..262143) is used to represent RNC_MP_ID.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_SCANNER_ID
parametertype.description: The scanner ID field consists of sequence of bits (24bits), each bit corresponding to a particular scanner ID (0…23 scanners GPEH, 0..15 scanners UETR, 0-1 scanners CTR). Sc. ID 1..24 (1= bit0... 24= bit23) Bit pos MSB 23, 22, 21 ... 2, 1, 0 LSB “0” is used in the corresponding bit location to indicate when an event is NOT part of a particular scanner. “1” will be used in the corresponding bit location to indicate that an event is part of a particular scanner. Note that the same event could be part of one, several, or all scanners. Event presence for each scanner will be indicated with “1” in the scanner ID field.
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_SOURCE_CONNECTION_PROPERTIES
parametertype.description: This parameter will be presented as a bit map value. Only the first 16 bits (LSB) are used. Bit 0 (LSB) indicates if CM in DL is used: 0=CM DL not used, 1=CM DL used. Bit 1 indicates if CM in UL is used: 0=CM UL not used, 1=CMin UL used.Bit 2 indicates TTI length if E-DCH is used: 0=10ms TTI(default value for non E-DCH connections), 1=2ms TTI. Bit 3 indicates if the connection is using EL2: 0=Fixed sizeRLC and MAC-hs used on HS-DSCH (non-EL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC-ehs on HS-DSCH (EL2). Bit 4 indicates if 64QAM is activated: 0 = 64QAM not activated, 1 = 64QAM activated. Bits 5 and 6 are used to represent speech categor y, where: 0= Not applicable (bit pattern ’00’) 1=AMR-NB MMMulti-rate. (bit pattern 01 ) 2=AMR-NB MM Single-rate 12.2 (bit pattern ’10’), 3=AMR NB MM Set to 1, (bit pattern 11 ). Bit 7 is reserved if MIMO is activated; 0=MIMO deactivated, 1=MIMO activated. Bit 8 indicates if SrbOnHs is used: 0 = SRB on X/DCH, 1 =SRB on X/HS. Bit 9 indicates if SrbOnEul is used: 0 = SRB on DCH/X, 1 =SRB on EUL/X. Bit 10 indicates if Multi Carrier is used/activated: 0= Multi Carrier is not used/activated, 1= Multi Carrier is used/activated. Bit 11 indicates if High Speed Downlink for FACH is used: 0 =HS-FACH is not used, 1 = HS-FACH is used. Bit 12 indicates if CPC is used: 0=CPC not used, 1=CPC used. Bit 13 indicates if Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is used/activated: 0 = Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is not used, 1 = Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is used. Bit 14 indicates if Enhanced UE DRX is used/activated: 0 = Enhanced UE DRX is not used, 1 = Enhanced UE DRX is used. Bit 15 indicates if the connection is using IL2: 0=Fixed sizeRLC and MAC-e/es used on E-DCH (non-IL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC-i/is on E-DCH (IL2). NOTE 1: If both Bit 4 and Bit 7 are active at the same time, the combination 64QAM+MIMO is used. NOTE 2: NO VALIDITY BIT IS USED!

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_SOURCE_CONNECTION_PROPERTIES_EXT
parametertype.description: Bitmap indicating conection properties for the source configuration: Bit 0 indicates if Enhanced Uplink for FACH is used: 0=EUL-FACH is not used, 1=EUL-FACH is used Bit 1 indicates if IU UP version 2 is used: 0=CIU UP version 1 is used, 1=IU UPversion 2 is used Bit 2 indicates if Dynamic RLC parameter configuration is used: 0=Dynamic RLCis not used, 1=Dynamic RLC is used Bit 3 indicates if Improved MAC-is/es Re-ordering is used: 0=Improved MAC-is/es is not used, 1=Improved MAC-is/es is used Bit 4 indicates if EUL Multi Carrier is used: 0=EUL Multi Carrier is not used, 1=EUL Multi Carrier is used Bit 5 is not used Bit 6 is not used Bit 7 indicates if Data Acceleration activation is requested: 0=Data Acceleration not requested, 1=Data Acceleration requested. Bits 8-15 are spare and are always 0. Note: No validity bit is used!

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_TOTAL_DL_CHAN_CODE_TREE_CONSUMPTION
parametertype.description: Total downlink channelization code tree consumption as percentage of the DL code tree in use. Number of DL codes reserved for HS-DSCH set by numHsPdschCodes is not included. Usage over total number of codes, including DL codes reserved for HS-DSCH, can be calculated as: EVENT_PARAM_TOTAL_DL_CHA_CODE_TREE_CONSUMPTION * [(16- numHsPdschCodes)/16] + (numHsPdschCodes /16)
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. Total downlink channelization code tree consumption as percentage of the DL code tree in use. parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_UE_IFLS_CAP
parametertype.description: The capabilities of UE related to IFLS. This parameter will be presented as a bit map value. Only the first 7 bits (LSB) are used, the rest are spare. For details on bitfield defintions, check the EventParamBitfieldDef sheet.
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. The capabilities of UE related to IFLS. This parameter is presented as a bit map value. Only the first 9 bits (LSB) are used, the rest are spare. Bit 0 indicates if UE is capable of Multi Carrier: 0=Not Multi Carrier Capable UE, 1=Multi Carrier Capable UE. Bit 1 indicates if UE is capable of Dual-band Multi Carrier: 0=Not Dual-band Multi Carrier Capable UE, 1=Dual-band Multi Carrier Capable UE. Bit 2 indicates if UE is capable of MIMO: 0=Not MMO capable UE, 1=MMO capable UE. Bit 3 indicates if UE is capable of EUL: 0=Not EUL capable UE, 1=EUL capable UE. Bit 4 indicates if UE is capable of HS: 0=Not HS capable UE, 1=HS capable UE. Bit 5 indicates if UE is capable of CPC: 0=Not CPC capable UE, 1=CPC capable UE. Bit 6 indicates if UE is capable of 64QAM: 0=Not CPC capable UE, 1=Not 64QAM capable UE. Bit 7 indicates if UE is capable of 3 Multi Carrier: 0=Not 3 Multi Carrier capable UE, 1=3 Multi Carrier: capable UE. Bit 8 indicates if UE is capable of Dual-band 3 Multi Carrier : 0=Not Dual-band 3 Multi Carrier capable UE, 1=Dual-band 3 Multi Carrier capable UE. Bits 9-15 are spare and is always 0.

parametertype.description: This parameter is related to EVENT_PARAM_FAILURE. That parameter specifies the type of failure and this parameter the corresponding value for the failure. Possible values for differend failure reasons: - cngstState = range: [UL, DL, UL+DL], - totAseUl = Uplink ASE load in the cell, range: 0 - 2000, - totAseDl = Downlink ASE load in the cell, range: 0 - 2000], - current SF = range: [8, 16, 32], - dlChCodeTreeUsage = Number of links with SF = x in the cell, range: 0-x, - (filteredDlPower+estimatedDlPwrDelta) - Consumed DL capacity credits if blocked by DL RBS HW resources or UL and DL RBS HW resources. Range: 0 - 131071. - Consumed UL capacity credits if blocked due to only UL RBS HW resources. Range: 0 - 131071. - EVENT_VALUE_TOO_MANY_USERS_ON_HSPDSCH Range: 0 - 1000. - Represents the number of E-DCH users in the serving cell in case of failure reason=EVENT_VALUE_TOO_MANY_SERVING_CELL_USERS_EUL. Range: 0 - 100. - Represents the number of E-DCH users in the non-serving cell in case of failure reason=EVENT_VALUE_TOO_MANY_NON_SERVING_CELL_USERS_EUL. Range: 0 - 100. - EVENT_VALUE_BLOCKED_BY_CONGESTION_CTRL. Range: 1-9, where: 1 = UL_OVERLOAD 2 = DL_DCH_OVERLOAD 3 = UL_AND_DL_DCH_OVERLOAD 4 = HSDSCH_OVERLOAD 5 = UL_AND_HSDSCH_OVERLOAD 8 = HSDSCH_AND_DL_DCH_OVERLOAD 9 = UL_AND_DL_DCH_AND_HSDSCH_OVERLOAD - TN_IUB failure reasons: Range 0..19900, Unit 100 kbit/s - Represents the number of radio links in case of failure reason=EVENT_VALUE_TOO_MANY_USERS_WITH_SFxx. Range: 0 - 256. SFxx = range: [4, 8, 16, 32, 64, 128]
parametertype.comment: RNC Application Mode=BOTH. This parameter is related to EVENT_PARAM_FAILURE, that specifies the type of failure, and this parameter the corresponding value for the failure. The following values are possible for different failure reasons: -cngstState = range: [UL, DL, UL+DL] -totAseUl = Uplink ASE load in the cell, range: [0 - 2000 ] -totAseDl = Downlink ASE load in the cell, range: [0 - 2000] -current SF = range: [8, 16, 32] -dlChCodeTreeUsage = Number of links with SF = x in the cell, range: [0-x] -(filteredDlPower+estimatedDlPwrDelta) -Consumed DL capacity credits if blocked by DL RBS HW resources or UL and DL RBS HW resources. Range: [0 - 131071] -Consumed UL capacity credits if blocked due to only UL RBS HW resources. Range: [0 - 131071] -EVENT_VALU E_TOO_MANY _USERS_ON_ HSPDSCH Range: [0 - 1000] -Represents the number of E-DCH users in the serving cell for failure reason=EVENT_VALU E_TOO_MANY_ SERVING_CELL_USERS_EUL. Range: [0 - 100] -Represents the number of E-DCH users in the non-serving cell for failure reason=EVENT_VALU E_TOO_MANY_ NON_SERVING_CELL_USERS_EUL. Range: [0 - 100] -EVENT_VALUE_BLOCKED_BY_CONGESTION_CTRL. Range: [1-9], where: 1 = UL_OVERLOAD 2 = DL_DCH_OVERLOAD 3 = UL_AND_DL_DCH_OVERLOAD 4 = HSDSCH_OVERLOAD 5 = UL_AND_HSDSCH_OVERLOAD 8 = HSDSCH_AND_DL_DCH_OVERLOAD 9 = UL_AND_DL_DCH_AND_HSDSCH_OVERLOAD -TN_IUB failure reasons: Range [0-19900], Unit 100 kbit/s -Represents the number of radio links for failure reason=EVENT_VALUE_TOO_MANY_USERS_WITH_SFxx. Range: 0 - 256. SFxx = range: [4, 8, 16, 32, 64, 128].

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_WANTED_CONNECTION_PROPERTIES
parametertype.description: This parameter will be presented as a bit map value. Only the first 16 bits (LSB) are used. Bit 0 (LSB) indicates if CM in DL is used: 0=CM DL not used, 1=CM DL used. Bit 1 indicates if CM in UL is used: 0=CM UL not used, 1=CMin UL used.Bit 2 indicates TTI length if E-DCH is used: 0=10ms TTI(default value for non E-DCH connections), 1=2ms TTI. Bit 3 indicates if the connection is using EL2: 0=Fixed sizeRLC and MAC-hs used on HS-DSCH (non-EL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC-ehs on HS-DSCH (EL2). Bit 4 indicates if 64QAM is activated: 0 = 64QAM not activated, 1 = 64QAM activated. Bits 5 and 6 are used to represent speech categor y, where: 0= Not applicable (bit pattern ’00’) 1=AMR-NB MMMulti-rate. (bit pattern 01 ) 2=AMR-NB MM Single-rate 12.2 (bit pattern ’10’), 3=AMR NB MM Set to 1, (bit pattern 11 ). Bit 7 is reserved if MIMO is activated; 0=MIMO deactivated, 1=MIMO activated. Bit 8 indicates if SrbOnHs is used: 0 = SRB on X/DCH, 1 =SRB on X/HS. Bit 9 indicates if SrbOnEul is used: 0 = SRB on DCH/X, 1 =SRB on EUL/X. Bit 10 indicates if Multi Carrier is used/activated: 0= Multi Carrier is not used/activated, 1= Multi Carrier is used/activated. Bit 11 indicates if High Speed Downlink for FACH is used: 0 =HS-FACH is not used, 1 = HS-FACH is used. Bit 12 indicates if CPC is used: 0=CPC not used, 1=CPC used. Bit 13 indicates if Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is used/activated: 0 = Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is not used, 1 = Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is used. Bit 14 indicates if Enhanced UE DRX is used/activated: 0 = Enhanced UE DRX is not used, 1 = Enhanced UE DRX is used. Bit 15 indicates if the connection is using IL2: 0=Fixed sizeRLC and MAC-e/es used on E-DCH (non-IL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC-i/is on E-DCH (IL2). NOTE 1: If both Bit 4 and Bit 7 are active at the same time, the combination 64QAM+MIMO is used. NOTE 2: The Connection Properties of the UeRc reported in EVENT_PARAM_WANTED_CONF. This parameter is not applicable for IRATHO, IRATCC or GAN HO. For CNHHO this parameter shall report the Connection Properties of the wanted target UeRc for the CNHHO. NOTE 3: NO VALIDITY BIT IS USED!

event.name: INTERNAL_SYSTEM_RELEASE
event.triggerdescription: Event Description: Captures each time one or several RABs or a standalone RRC connection is released and the release is not a normal release. Event Trigger: Triggered for each system-initiated release of a RAB or Uu connection when one of the following conditions is met: - RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMMAND message received from the CN with 'release cause' set to anything other than 'Normal Release', 'Successful Relocation', 'Resource Optimisation Relocation', 'User Inactivity', 'no-remaining-rab' or 'UE generated signalling connection release', except when the message is received from the PS CN with 'release cause' set to 'UTRAN Generated Reason'; - RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMMAND message received from the PS CN with 'release cause' set to 'UTRAN Generated Reason', if the RNC earlier sent an Iu Release Request to the PS CN with cause set to Normal Release', 'Successful Relocation', 'Resource Optimisation Relocation', 'User Inactivity', 'no-remaining-rab' or 'UE generated signalling connection release'; - Successful RAB release after reception of RANAP: RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message from the CN with 'release cause' set to anything other than 'Normal Release', 'Successful Relocation', 'Resource Optimisation Relocation', 'User Inactivity' or 'no-remaining-rab'; - RNC sends a RANAP RESET RESOURCE message to the CN; - RANAP: RESET message received from the CN; - Detection in the RNC of RANAP Service Unavailable. One event is triggered per CN node if system release conditions are applicable.

event.name: INTERNAL_PS_RELEASE_DUE_TO_CNHHO

event.name: INTERNAL_PACKET_DEDICATED_THROUGHPUT
event.triggerdescription: The event periodically (every 2 seconds) reports the UL/DL data rate separately for all RB's on the transport channel (more than one RB on the transport channel in case of MAC-d multiplexing). The UL/DL throughput for PS interactive data only reported for these transport channels DCH/E-DCH/HS-DSCH (i.e. no reporting when the PS RB is carried over FACH/RACH). The events are scheduled in the same order each time (every 2s) so that it is possible to follow the throughput per RB (more than one RB on the transport channel in case of MAC-d multiplexing).

event.name: INTERNAL_CALL_SETUP_FAIL
event.triggerdescription: Event Description: Captured for each failed CS or PS call setup attempt. Event Trigger: Triggered either at sending of RAB Assignment Response indicating failure to setup or modify RABs or when a signalling connection is released and the release is not a normal release. A call setup attempt can be detected from the establishment cause in RRC Connection Request, Cell Update or Initial Direct Transfer or through reception of RAB Assignment Request with the IE ‘RABs to be setup or modifi Triggered for each failed CS or PS call setup attempt when one of the following conditions is met: - Failure to establish RRC Connection after RRC Connection Request for a CS or PS call setup attempt (1, 2) - System-initiated release (3) of a signaling connection during the NAS signaling sequence (4) at call setup towards a CS or PS CN (1, 2), if an RRC Connection Request, Cell Update or Initial Direct Transfer containing the IE 'establisment cause' was received prior to the NAS signaling sequence. - RANAP Rab Assignment Response message sent to the CN indicating failure to setup or modify RABs. (1) A call setup attempt towards the CS CN has RRC establishment cause equal to 'Emergency Call', 'Originating', 'Originating Conversational Call' or 'Terminating Conversational Call'. (2) A call setup attempt towards the PS CN has RRC establishment cause equal to 'Originating Interactive Call', 'Terminating Interactive Call', 'Originating Background Call', 'Terminating Background Call' or 'Originating Subscribed Traffic Call'. (3) A system-initiated release can be triggered by: - a RANAP Reset message received from the CN; - a RANAP Iu Release Command message received from the CN with 'release cause' set to anything other than 'Normal Release', 'Successful Relocation', 'Resource Optimisation Relocation', 'User Inactivity' or 'no-remaining-rab'; - a RAB Assignment Request message received from the CN with 'release cause' set to anything other than 'Normal Release', 'Successful Relocation', 'Resource Optimisation Relocation', or 'User Inactivity'; - the RNC when sending a RANAP Reset Resource message to the CN; - detection in the RNC of RANAP Service Unavailable. (4) The NAS signaling sequence is defined as the phase starting with IU Signaling Connection establishment and ending with RAB Assignment Request. One event is triggered per CN node if system release conditions are applicable.

event.name: INTERNAL_NORMAL_RELEASE
event.triggerdescription: Event Description: Captures each time one or several RABs or a Uu connection is released and the release is a normal release. Event Trigger: Triggered for each normal-initiated release of a RAB or Uu connection when one of the following conditions is met: - RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMMAND message received from the CN with 'release cause' set to 'Normal Release', 'Successful Relocation', 'Resource Optimisation Relocation', 'User Inactivity', 'no-remaining-rab' or 'UE generated signalling connection release'; - RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMMAND message received from the PS CN with 'release cause' set to 'UTRAN Generated Reason', if the RNC earlier sent an Iu Release Request to the PS CN with cause set to Normal Release', 'Successful Relocation', 'Resource Optimisation Relocation', 'User Inactivity', 'no-remaining-rab' or 'UE generated signalling connection release'; - Successful RAB release after reception of RANAP:RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message from the CN with 'release cause' set to either of 'Normal Release', 'Successful Relocation', 'Resource Optimisation Relocation', 'User Inactivity' or 'no-remaining-rab' One event is triggered per CN node if normal release conditions are applicable

event.name: INTERNAL_OUT_HARD_HANDOVER_FAILURE
event.triggerdescription: Event Description: Captures failed outgoing hard handover attemps Event Trigger: Triggered for any failure case during an outgoing hard handover (Inter-RAT Handover, Inter-RAT Cell Change, Inter-Frequency Handover and Core Network Hard Handover) from the start of the handover execution until the termination of procedure. An outgoing Hard Handover failure can lead to that he Uu Connection is either released or reverted to the source Active Set and configuration.

event.name: INTERNAL_RES_CPICH_ECNO
event.triggerdescription: The event shall be triggered periodically based on RES measurement periodicity. Additionally it shall be triggered at call set up. Event only visible in GPEH if: GEO-W (FAJ 121 1475), Geo-Observability Data (FAJ 121 1470) and MRR-W (FAJ 121 993) optional features are available.
event.osscomment: Not displayed in the PMS GUI! Only as part of the RES Pos feature

event.name: INTERNAL_CN_OVERLOAD_CONTROL_STATUS
event.triggerdescription: Whenever RNC receives a RANAP Overload message, and timer T(IGOR) is stopped.

event.name: INTERNAL_LOAD_CONTROL_ACTION
event.triggerdescription: Triggered when Load Control, congType = lc (load control) have been executed in UEH for each Ue

event.name: INTERNAL_LOAD_CONTROL_TRIGGER
event.triggerdescription: Triggered when Load Control, congType = lc (lod control) has been initiated on cell level.

event.name: INTERNAL_INC_EXT_HARD_HANDOVER_SUCCESS
event.triggerdescription: The event shall be triggered per core network at incoming hard handover from external node, when the RANAP Relocation Complete with RABs successfully setup is sent to the core network.

event.name: INTERNAL_INC_EXT_HARD_HANDOVER_FAILURE
event.triggerdescription: Event Description: Captures successful outgoing hard handover Event Trigger: Triggered per failed incoming hard handover (Inter-RAT Handover and Core Network Hard Handover) from external node, when sending RANAP Relocation Request Acknowledge (including IE RABs Failed to Setup List), RANAP Relocation Failure or IU Release Request indicating RAB failure.

event.name: INTERNAL_AMR_MAX_RATE_RESTRICTION
event.triggerdescription: The event is to observe AMR NB MM and WB max rate restriction settings in RRC: Transport Format Combination Control, RRC: Radio Bearer Setup for speech AMR MM MR+LR and AMR WB and Iu User Plane: Rate Control RNC to CN.

event.name: INTERNAL_IFLS_NO_CANDIDATE_EVALUATION
event.triggerdescription: The event is triggered everytime when RNC enter IFLS but RNC do not continue with an evaluation of the candidate cells and IFLS attempt stopped due to some reason

event.name: INTERNAL_IFLS_EVALUATION_RESULT
event.triggerdescription: The event is triggered everytime RNC enter IFLS and evaluate the candidate cells that can attempt to load share to.

event.name: INTERNAL_ANR_ADD_RELATION_PREVENTED
event.triggerdescription: The GPEH Event is sent by the ANR feature when it is prevented to Add a Neighbour Cell Relation in the MOM database. The relation can be of any type, e.g. Intra-Frequency. The reason why the Relation couldn’t be created is given. The reason is given as a value. Value 0 is the highest priority reason. It is not possible to indicate several reasons at the same time. This means that if value 0 is given, it is unknown if value 1 etc are also true.

event.name: INTERNAL_EVENT_5A
event.triggerdescription: The event is triggered when the amount of bad CRCs during a predefined sliding window exceeds a predefined value. The event is only visible if MRR-W (FAJ 121 993) and UE Quality Measurement Event 5A (FAJ121 3930) optional features are available.
event.osscomment: Not displayed in the PMS GUI! Only as part of the UE Quality Measurement Event 5A

event.name: INTERNAL_ACCESS_CLASS_BARRING
event.triggerdescription: Provided that the license for Automatically Triggered Access Class Barring on Cell Level (FAJ 121 3946) is active and UtranCell::autoAcbEnabled = TRUE, this event is triggered at a periodicity given as a multiple of 10 seconds, where the multiplicity can be 1-6 times.
